It seems that typescript can't resolve the types from `'../src/runtime/control.js'` in `@sveltejs/kit/types/index.d.ts`.
Creating a new `d.ts` file in the `@sveltejs/kit/src/runtime` directory and importing the `ValidationError` there seems to work.

`@sveltejs/kit/src/runtime/test.d.ts`:
```ts
import { ValidationError } from './control.js';

type UnpackValidationError<T> = T extends ValidationError<infer X> ? X : T;

type ValErr = ValidationError<{test: string}>

type UnpackedValErr = UnpackValidationError<ValErr>
// UnpackedValErr = { test: string; }
```
